QUES: SQL command to show the name, continent and population of all countries.
----------------SELECT name, continent, population FROM world.

QUES: Show the name for the countries that have a population of at least 200 million. 200 million is 200000000, there are eight zeros.
-----------------SELECT name FROM world WHERE population > 200000000

QUES: Give the name and the per capita GDP for those countries with a population of at least 200 million.
-----------------SELECT name, gdp=gdp/population FROM world WHERE population > 200000000

QUES: Show the name and population in millions for the countries of the continent 'South America'. Divide the population by 1000000 to get population in millions.
---------------SELECT name, population=population/1000000 FROM world WHERE continent = 'South America'  
       
